text: One of the most important places in the Delaware Valley during my teen years.

text: For the over 21's, the Troc used to also host amazing movie nights where you could watch popcorn flicks from the 80s and have a bucket of beers at a reasonable price. Think @hoglundan went once during a trip to Philly.

text: The history as a burlesque house was great. I remember telling my grandmom that I was headed there for a show once in high school and she freaked out b/c I wasn't aware of the history and she wasn't aware of the change to a music venue in the 80s
